# AI ERP System — Windsurf Rules

See `.ai/instructions.md` for full project conventions.

## Quick Reference

- **Stack**: TypeScript, React 19, Express, tRPC v11, Drizzle ORM, MySQL, Tailwind v4
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (NOT npm/yarn)
- **Module System**: ESM

## Commands

- `pnpm run dev` — Start dev server
- `pnpm run build` — Production build
- `pnpm run check` — Type check
- `pnpm run test` — Run tests
- `pnpm run format` — Prettier
- `pnpm run db:push` — DB migrations

## Structure

- `client/src/` — React frontend (components, pages, hooks)
- `server/` — tRPC routers + `_core/` services
- `shared/` — Shared types (re-exported from drizzle schema)
- `drizzle/schema.ts` — Single database schema file

## Key Rules

- All code in TypeScript with strict mode — no `any`
- Use pnpm for all package operations
- Use Drizzle ORM — no raw SQL
- Use tRPC procedures with Zod validation for all API endpoints
- Frontend uses shadcn/ui patterns, Tailwind CSS, wouter routing
- Tests in `server/**/*.test.ts` using Vitest
- Run `pnpm run check` before committing
- Path aliases: `@/*` → `client/src/*`, `@shared/*` → `shared/*`
- Never commit `.env` files
